Problem: Finding the non-equal nearest neighbours on both the sides of an array element and comparing those values to decide a peak or valley. It is simple if we there are no duplicate values next to each.

For the adjacent duplicates we have to keep track of the closest neighbour on left and not update it till duplicates are crossed. 

Once the adjacent duplicates are done, we can update it for the newer values .

```
public int countHillValley(int[] nums) {
        int ans = 0;
        int prev = nums[0];
        for(int i = 1; i < nums.length-1; i++){
            if((nums[i] > nums[i+1] && nums[i] > prev || (nums[i] < nums[i+1] && nums[i] < prev)))
                ans++;
            if(nums[i] != nums[i+1]){
                prev = nums[i];
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
	```

