we dont care about the number of indeces in valleys and hills, so remove all adjacent elements of same value. Then loop through the resultant array.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. create a new array where no element is of same value and are adjacent. 
2. iterate starting from idx 1 and till one before last and check if each idx you are at is either bigger or smaller its left and right neighbors. 
3. if so, add to the result

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
2 * O(n) since we loop through array twice, discard constant -> so O(n)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n) since we create another array of potentially size equal to the original array.

