# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
I thought for a long time, how to do it better than brute force solution, but anything didn't came in my mind. So, i decided to write the brute force solution.So, while writing i came up with a thought that if a guard has already visited a particular cell in that direction, then the cell is guarded, if any others guard is present in the path in that direction, so he need not to visit all the cells in that direction, G----G----- i.e if the path is visited by one guard while in that direction, other guard need not to travel in the same direction as all path are already visited by first guard


Let us try to understand it!
G..........
the path first guard visited in that direction.
if after, there is also a guard in that path
G...G...... he need not to visit the cell in that direction

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. A matrix of size m*n is created and intialised to 0
2. To check for the walls, it is marked as 1
3. We start iterate over the guards

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n*m)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n*m)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int countUnguarded(int m, int n, vector<vector<int>>& guards, vector<vector<int>>& walls) {
        int arr[m][n], count = 0;
        for(int i = 0 ; i < m ; i++){
            for(int j = 0 ; j < n ; j++) arr[i][j] = 0;
        }

        for(auto &it : walls){
            arr[it[0]][it[1]] = 1;
        }

        // if left = 3, right = 4, top = 5, bottom = 6;

        for(auto &it : guards){
            int row = it[0], col = it[1];
            arr[row][col] = 2;
            //travelling towards upward, break if guard is present, wall, already traverse by some guard in that direction.
            for(int i = row-1 ; i >= 0 ; i--){
                if(arr[i][col] == 1 || arr[i][col] == 2 || arr[i][col] == 5) break;
                arr[i][col] = 5; 
            }
            //traversing towards downward
            for(int i = row+1 ; i < m ; i++){
                if(arr[i][col] == 1 || arr[i][col] == 2 || arr[i][col] == 6) break;
                arr[i][col] = 6;
            }
            //traversing towards left
            for(int j = col-1; j >= 0 ; j--){
                if(arr[row][j] == 1 || arr[row][j] == 2 || arr[row][j] == 3) break;
                arr[row][j] = 3;
            }
            //traversing towards right
            for(int j = col+1; j < n ; j++){
                if(arr[row][j] == 1 || arr[row][j] == 2 || arr[row][j] == 4) break;
                arr[row][j] = 4;
            }
        }

        for(int i = 0; i < m ; i++){
            for(int j = 0 ; j < n ; j++){
                if(arr[i][j] == 0) count++;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
};
```

