Step 1. Setup the grid assigning walls and guards to their respective positions
Step 2. Loop through the grid and append to our lists so that each of our row and column lists are in sorted order
Step 3. Loop through the grid again and if we see and empty column binary search for guards left/right and up/down from our posion using the lists we setup in step 2
Step 4. If we do not see any guards add 1 to the result. At the end return our result


