# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Simply loop thourgh all guards to see how many cells are watched. 

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Use a ```vector<string> cells``` to store the states of cells: 
- 'w': cell occupied by a wall
- 'g': cell occupied by a guard
- 'h': cell watched horizonally
- 'v': cell watched vertically
- 'b': cell watched both horizonally & vertically
- 'u': cell unwatched and unoccupied

'h' and 'v' are defined to reduce redundant check.  

We assume that all cells are 'u' at first. Thus the result would be initialized as ```int res = m * n;```

First step, mark all walls and guards. Everytime a cell is occupied, ```--res;```

Second step, go through all ```guards``` to mark watched cells. When going vertically, switch case the cell
- 'u': subtract ```res``` and mark it as 'v';
- 'v' or 'b': cell has been checked by another guard, so this cell and all other cells vertically after it do not need to be checked
- 'w': there is a wall, so this cell and all cells vertically after it are not watched by this guard
- 'h': this cell is watched horizonally, so ```res``` should not decrease by 1; despite, we are not sure whether the cells vertically after it is checked, so the loop should go on

The horizonal checking is similar to the steps above. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
Worst case $O(m*n)$: when guards are placed across all rows and columns

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$O(m*n)$, the recording strings

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int countUnguarded(int m, int n, vector<vector<int>>& guards, vector<vector<int>>& walls) {
        vector<string> cells(m, string(n, 'u')); // unguarded
        int res = m*n;
        for ( vector<int>& w: walls ){
            --res;
            cells[w[0]][w[1]] = 'w';
        }
        for ( vector<int>& g: guards ){
            --res;
            cells[g[0]][g[1]] = 'g';
        }
        for ( vector<int>& g: guards ){
            bool stop = false;
            for ( int i = g[0]-1; ~i && !stop ; --i ){
                char& c = cells[i][g[1]];
                switch ( c ){
                    case 'u': {--res; c = 'v';} break;
                    case 'h': c = 'b'; break;
                    default: stop = true;
                }
            }
            stop = false;
            for ( int i = g[0]+1; i != m && !stop ; ++i ){
                char& c = cells[i][g[1]];
                switch ( c ){
                    case 'u': {--res; c = 'v';} break;
                    case 'h': c = 'b'; break;
                    default: stop = true;
                }
            }
            stop = false;
            for ( int j = g[1]-1; ~j && !stop ; --j ){
                char& c = cells[g[0]][j];
                switch ( c ){
                    case 'u': {--res; c = 'h';} break;
                    case 'v': c = 'b'; break;
                    default: stop = true;
                }
            }
            stop = false;
            for ( int j = g[1]+1; j != n && !stop ; ++j ){
                char& c = cells[g[0]][j];
                switch ( c ){
                    case 'u': {--res; c = 'h';} break;
                    case 'v': c = 'b'; break;
                    default: stop = true;
                }
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

