# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Try to solve problem in $$O(m*n)$$ time complexity.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Create matrix, a, and first add 16 in cell where are the guards and 23 in cells where are the walls. Set 0 to the rest of the cells. Iterate through matrix from left, right, top, bottom, and remember did we encouter Wall or Guard in that row/ column.
If we last encountered Guard that means that that cell is guarded. We use different number to clarify from which side the cell is guarded: 0x1000 from left, 0b0100 from right, 0b0010 from top, 0b0001 from bottom. Add the end we count unguarded cells.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(m*n)$$

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(m*n)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int countUnguarded(int m, int n, vector<vector<int>>& guards, vector<vector<int>>& walls) {
        int a[m][n];
        for (int i = 0; i < m; ++i) {
            for (int j = 0; j < n; ++j) {
                a[i][j] = 0;
            }
        }
        for (auto& g : guards) {
            a[g[0]][g[1]] = 16;
        }
        for (auto& w : walls) {
            a[w[0]][w[1]] = 32;
        }
        char cur = 'X';
        // pass from left
        for (int i = 0; i < m; ++i) {
            cur = 'X';
            for (int j = 0; j < n; ++j) {
                if (a[i][j] == 16) {
                    cur = 'G';
                }
                else if (a[i][j] == 32) {
                    cur = 'W';
                }
                else {
                    if (cur == 'G') {
                        a[i][j] = a[i][j] | 0b1000;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        // pass from right
        for (int i = 0; i < m; ++i) {
            cur = 'X';
            for (int j = n - 1; j >= 0; --j) {
                if (a[i][j] == 16) {
                    cur = 'G';
                }
                else if (a[i][j] == 32) {
                    cur = 'W';
                }
                else {
                    if (cur == 'G') {
                        a[i][j] = a[i][j] | 0b0100;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        // pass from top
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            cur = 'X';
            for (int j = 0; j < m; ++j) {
                if (a[j][i] == 16) {
                    cur = 'G';
                }
                else if (a[j][i] == 32) {
                    cur = 'W';
                }
                else {
                    if (cur == 'G') {
                        a[j][i] = a[j][i] | 0b0010;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        // pass from bottom
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            cur = 'X';
            for (int j = m - 1; j >= 0; --j) {
                if (a[j][i] == 16) {
                    cur = 'G';
                }
                else if (a[j][i] == 32) {
                    cur = 'W';
                }
                else {
                    if (cur == 'G') {
                        a[j][i] = a[j][i] | 0b0001;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        int count = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < m; ++i) {
            for (int j = 0; j < n; ++j) {
                if (a[i][j] == 0) {
                    ++count;
                }
            }
        }

        return count;
    }
};
```

