solutions.content:
The problem is a simple **DFS** problem where you traverse in a all **4-directions** without any **turn** and mark all the cells as **visible** in the process.
After marking all the cell visible you need to traverse the matrix and find count of all **hidden** cells.

# **Why does TLE happens?**

 **TLE** occurs because you are processing for some of the **cells** which are already marked as **visible**. This ***extra work*** can be eleminiated if you reach a already marked **visible** cell and you check if the **direction** in which this cell was marked is the **same** **direction** your current **DFS** call is moving in, if **yes** then **no** need to mark further as the cells ahead are already marked with some previous **DFS** call which marked the current cell

 *Note the overlaps of colors in bottom right right matrix state:*

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/4b00679b-4c3e-4e1b-8f45-f735d8119cad_1665672976.6947653.png)




```
typedef pair<int,int> pr;
class Solution {
public:
    int n,m;
    int dx[4]={-1,1,0,0};
    int dy[4]={0,0,-1,1};

    int countUnguarded(int sz1, int sz2, vector<vector<int>>& g, vector<vector<int>>& w) {

        n=sz1;m=sz2;
        vector<vector<pr>> a(n,vector<pr>(m,{1,-1}));

        for(auto i:w) a[i[0]][i[1]].first=0;
        queue<pair<pr,int> > q;

        // 2->Guard , 1->Empty , 0->Wall 3->Visible

        for(auto i:g) a[i[0]][i[1]].first=2,q.push({{i[0],i[1]},4});

        while(!q.empty()){

            auto curr=q.front().first;
            int dir=q.front().second;
            q.pop();

            int x=curr.first,y=curr.second;

            a[x][y].first=3;a[x][y].second=dir;

            for(int i=0;i<4;i++){
                int x1=x+dx[i],y1=y+dy[i];

                if(x1<0 || y1<0 || x1>n-1 || y1>m-1) continue;

                if(a[x1][y1].first==2 || a[x1][y1].first==0) continue;

                if(a[x1][y1].first==3 && a[x1][y1].second==dir) continue;

                if(dir==i || dir==4) q.push({ {x1,y1} ,i });

            }

        }

        int ans=0;for(auto i:a) for(auto j:i) if(j.first==1) ans++;return ans;

    }
};
```

