# Approach
I made this wayyyy more complicated than it needed to be. 

Find the number of times the letter occurs in the string by splitting the string into an array and then filtering the array for the letter. 

Return this value as a percentage by dividing it by string length * 100. 

/**
 * @param {string} s
 * @param {character} letter
 * @return {number}
 */

var percentageLetter = function(s, letter) {
    const value = s.split('').filter((x) => x === letter).length;
    return Math.floor((value / s.length) * 100)
};

```

