# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We need calculate the income that will be deducted each time we loop through the brackets. By subtracting the current upper bound from the prev upper bound I am able to compare that value against what the current income is and select the minimum. 

eg. if I only have 1 dollar left of income but up to 4 dollars can be used in this tax bracket I want to only use the income I have left.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
