#### Simulation
We pick two largest piles, and fill two cups (or one, if we have only one pile left).

**C++**
```cpp
int fillCups(vector<int>& a) {
    int res = 0;
    for (; max({a[0], a[1], a[2]}) > 0; ++res) {
        sort(begin(a), end(a));
        --a[2];
        --a[1];
    }
    return res;
}
```
#### Formula
If we have one pile much larger than the others, the number of seconds will be the same as the number of cups in that large pile.

Or, if piles are of similar size, and we can always fill two cups, we will need `(a[0] + a[1] + a[2] + 1) / 2` seconds (we do `+ 1` in case the sum of cups is odd).

**C++**
```cpp
int fillCups(vector<int>& a) {
    return max({a[0], a[1], a[2], (a[0] + a[1] + a[2] + 1) / 2});
}
```

