Hi EveryOne , In this I am going to solve this question using basic mathematics.
**Time Complexity O(n) and Space Complexity O(1)**

**Equation 1->**  ```Each second we fill (either different or same cup) we cannot reduce the amount of  cups(of one type) to be filled by more than 1 so we need atleast max(amount) seconds to fill all solution. Got it ? So sol>=max(amount)```
**Equation 2 ->**  ```what will be minimum second required if we fill 2 cups each second then we will need ceil((total amount to fill)/2) So Solution would be Sol>=((total+1)/2)```

	Overall solution should satisfy both equations.

