Let's take an example 
i/p :
amount = [2,3,9]
In this example, instead of calculating all the calculations, I just took the addition of all elements if that is less than a maximum element of the amount, then return the maximum element of the amount vector.
i/p :
amount = [8,9,13]
In this example, the sum of the first two elements is greater than the maximum element, so I took the addition of all elements, if it is odd then just return (sum / 2) + 1, else return sum/2.
```
class Solution {
public:
    int fillCups(vector<int>& amount) 
    {
        sort(amount.begin(), amount.end());
        if(amount[0] + amount[1] <= amount[2])
            return amount[2];
        else
        {
            int cnt = amount[0] + amount[1] + amount[2];
            if(cnt % 2 == 1)
            {
                return (cnt/2) + 1;
            }
            else
            {
                return cnt/2;
            }
        }
    }
};
```

