# Intuition
Just keep filling the least and most required cups together

# Approach
Sort the array. Keep removing the smallest value and the largest value by 1, until the smallest one is zero, then increase the answer by the left out max value

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(smallest value)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int fillCups(int[] amount) {
        Arrays.sort(amount);
        int ans = 0;
        int lo=0, hi=2;
        if(amount[0] == 0) lo++;
        if(lo==1 && amount[1]==0) return amount[2];

        else if(lo==1){
            ans += amount[hi];
            return ans;
        }
        while(amount[lo] != 0){
            ans++;
            amount[lo]--;
            amount[hi]--;
            if(amount[hi-1] > amount[hi]){
                int temp = amount[hi-1];
                amount[hi-1] = amount[hi];
                amount[hi] = temp;
            }
        }

        ans += amount[2];
        return ans;
    }
}
```

