If at least 2 piles have unflipped cups, then choose the option to flip 2 cups per turn, else flip 1 cup.
So, we're gonna use a max heap to store the piles in descending order.

```
    public int fillCups(int[] amount) {
        Queue<Integer> heap = new PriorityQueue<>((a, b) -> b - a);
        for (int n : amount) {
            heap.offer(n);
        }

        int turns = 0;
        while (heap.peek() > 0) {
            int max = heap.poll();
            if (heap.peek() > 0) {
                int secondMax = heap.poll();
                heap.offer(secondMax - 1);
            }
            heap.offer(max - 1);
            turns++;
        }

        return turns;
    }
