solutions.content:
**Explanation:**
We need to deduct from the 2 types of cups that are highest in number, so we sort the array in descending order each time after deduction and count the number of times we had to deduct.
Since the array has only 3 elements, sorting will take negligible time.

**Code:**
```
int fillCups(vector<int>& amount) {
        int counter=0;
        sort(amount.rbegin(), amount.rend());
        if(amount[0]==0)
            return 0;
        while(amount[0]>0){
            amount[0]-=1;
            amount[1]-=1;
            counter++;
            sort(amount.rbegin(), amount.rend());
        }
        return counter;
    }
```

