# Intuition
You need to maximize the time you spend filling multiple cups simultaneously. To accomplish this, always fill the two largest sets of unfilled cups.

# Approach
1. Create a max heap with the elements in amount. In C#, the closest thing to a heap is a priority queue.
2. Until you have 1 element in the heap, dequeue the 2 largest values in the heap. Decrement both values and requeue them if they are not 0.
3. Repeat.

# Code
```
public class Solution {
    public int FillCups(int[] amount) {
        int seconds = 0;

        //max heap
        PriorityQueue<int, int> pq = new();

        //populate heap
        foreach (int i in amount) {
            if (i > 0) {
                pq.Enqueue(i, -1 * i);
            }
        }

        while (pq.Count != 0) {
            if (pq.Count == 1) {
                //you can no longer fill 2 cups simultaneously.
                int x = pq.Dequeue();

                seconds += x;
            } else {
                //fill 2 largest cups.
                int a = pq.Dequeue() - 1;
                int b = pq.Dequeue() - 1;

                if (a > 0)
                    pq.Enqueue(a, -1*a);

                if (b > 0)
                    pq.Enqueue(b, -1*b);

                seconds++;
            }
        }

        return seconds;
    }


}
```

